1. A toothbrush head comprising:
a neck having a long axis, the neck configured for releasable attachment to an electric toothbrush;
an elliptical shaped support member having a top surface and a bottom surface;
a drive mechanism for oscillating the support member; and
a plurality of tufts that have different heights as measured from a horizontal plane taken through the lowest point on the top surface, the plurality of tufts including curved, elongated tufts extending from the top surface, the curved tufts being disposed at each furthest edge of the support member, end tufts extending from the top surface, the end tufts being disposed inboard of the curved tufts, side tufts extending from the top surface, the side tufts being disposed at the edge of the support member, and inner tufts arranged in a ring and extending from the top surface, the inner tufts being disposed inboard of the side tufts and the end tufts, such that the curved tufts are taller in height than the end tufts which are taller in height than the side tufts,

6. A toothbrush head comprising:
a neck configured for releasable attachment to an electric toothbrush;
an elliptical shaped support having a top surface and a bottom surface, wherein the support member is elongated and includes a long axis and a short axis, a proximal end adjacent the neck and a distal end distal from the neck;
a drive mechanism for oscillating the support member; and
a plurality of tufts, the plurality of tufts including first and second sets of end tufts extending from the top surface, the first set of end tufts being disposed inboard of the proximal end of the support member and the second set being disposed inboard of the distal end of the support member; a first and second set of side tufts extending from the top surface, the first set of side tufts being disposed directly opposite the second set of side tufts along an edge of the support member; inner tufts arranged in a ring and extending from the top surface, the inner tufts being disposed inboard of the side tufts and the end tufts; and at least four elastomeric elements circumferentially spaced on the edge of the support member, each elastomeric element being disposed adjacent at least one of the side tufts
